Disney and Rian Johnson deconstructed the essence of what Star Wars means to so many people and replaced it with a depressing punch to the gut for no reason other than to have something new and novel. It disrespected all continuity that came before it while wrapping itself in a cloak of Star Wars flavored cynicism while still having the nerve to call itself a Star Wars movie.
The fact they Johnson tried to insert so much inappropriate flat humor in a movie with such a high death toll is shocking. The scenes weren\'t funny; and even if they were should we be laughing where everyone we are supposed to care about is dying on some level? Ultimately it succeeded in sending the message that everything in Star Wars is trivial except Rian Johnson\'s nihilistic contribution. Everyone is disposable.
I\'m not a Buddhist but I think if he was trying to send a non attachment lesson with a Buddhist flavor I would say he completely missed the boat.
He succeeded in sending a very negative message of how to care ( or not care) for those we have grown up with ( ie: all the characters up to this point) and it certainly isn\'t the kind of message that\'s consistent to Star Wars.
'

I believe I can show that the current audience score of 49% which RT displays for the Last Jedi is false. I can only speculate as to why they are lying but they clearly are. I did a statistical analysis of all of the audience reviews I was allowed to view. There are nearly 2000 pages of reviews and I was able to access 46 of them. This is a perfectly reasonable sample size which I believe represents an accurate reflection of the overall audience opinion. A five star rating system translated to a scale of 1 to 100 means that each star is worth 20 points. A half star is 10 points etc. Here are my results...

.5 stars - 339
1 star - 173
1.5 stars - 66
2 stars - 90
2.5 stars - 23
3 stars - 19
3.5 stars- 12
4 stars - 26
4.5 stars 25
5 stars 95

A sample size of 868 audience reviewers awarded a total of 23390 points for an average user score of 33.8594. Less than 34%.

I don\'t know why RT is lying to the public
column34: but they are clearly preventing the audience score from falling below a certain level. If RT is protecting Disney\'s interests then this is a conflict of interest of the highest order and this site cannot be trusted. Again
column35: the true audience score for this film is well
column36: WELL below 40. Avoid this movie. Cherish the OT and ignore these cash grab rip offs. '
